commText: Rahul and Padikkal are at the crease. Rahul is on strike. N Thushara will open the attack
N Thushara to Rahul, no run, full outswinger just outside off, Rahul defends
N Thushara to Rahul, 1 run, 132.8kph fuller than a length on middle and leg, hint of outswing, and Rahul glances it to fine leg

Struck on the pad and up goes the finger. Padikkal has taken the review. It's a full inswinger on middle, Padikkal looks to flick it away but is beaten on the inside edge before getting hit low on the front pad. Ball-tracking says it would've crashed into middle and leg. Three reds.
N Thushara to Padikkal, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

N Thushara to Padikkal, out Lbw!! Struck on the pad and up goes the finger. Padikkal has taken the review. It's a full inswinger on middle, Padikkal looks to flick it away but is beaten on the inside edge before getting hit low on the front pad. Ball-tracking says it would've crashed into middle and leg. Three reds. So it's a golden duck to close out a miserable season for the left-hander. Padikkal lbw b N Thushara 0(1)
Marcus Stoinis, right handed bat, comes to the crease
N Thushara to Stoinis, wide, full delivery straying a long way down leg, Stoinis can't reach it
N Thushara to Stoinis, wide, again down the leg-side, and Kishan makes a diving stop
N Thushara to Stoinis, 1 run, 132kph length ball on middle, Stoinis looks to defend but drags it off a thick inside edge past leg stump. He expected a bit of outswing, but it went on straight
N Thushara to Rahul, no run, fuller than a length on middle, defended forward
N Thushara to Rahul, no run, pitched up just outside off, 135.2kph, Rahul gets forward and punches sweetly. But it's straight to short cover
Deep backward square and fine leg are in place as Tendulkar runs in
Arjun Tendulkar, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, no run, length ball on middle and leg, inswinger, and Stoinis defends it down the pitch

Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, no run, 130.6kph length ball on off stump, swinging back in, Stoinis hangs back and punches gently to cover

Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, no run, oh Stoinis is given out LBW and he takes the review quickly. Was that too high? Length ball on middle and leg, swings in and hits him pretty high on the back leg as he hangs back to defend. Ball tracking confirms it would've gone over the stumps. Not a great decision from the onfield ump
Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, no run, full ball just outside off, Stoinis goes for a big drive but drags it off a thick inside edge onto pad
Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, 2 runs, banged in short, gets up to head height and Stoinis drags the pull through midwicket. Didn't time it all that well
Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, wide, full inswinger straying down leg, Stoinis misses
Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, no run, good length on middle, inswinger, and Stoinis defends down the pitch. Tendulkar picks it up and pretends to have a shy at the stumps. Stoinis is greatly amused
N Thushara to Rahul, 1 run, overpitched on middle and leg, Rahul knocks it to mid-on
N Thushara to Stoinis, FOUR, slower ball floated up on off, right in the slot for Stoinis who picks up the variation and hammers it back down the ground, straight over the bowler's head
N Thushara to Stoinis, no run, full and wide, outswinger, Stoinis reaches out but is beaten on the outside edge
N Thushara to Stoinis, no run, 136.1kph length ball on the pads, Stoinis clips it to midwicket
LSG's opening partnerships in IPL 2024 \nFirst 7 matches - Run: 279, Avg: 39.85, RR: 9.14, HS: 134 \nNext 7 matches - Run: 50, Avg: 7.14, RR: 6.97, HS: 20
Stoinis pulls out late, and points at the spider cam as the reason for him to do so
N Thushara to Stoinis, 1 run, length ball on middle and leg, Stoinis hangs back and punches wide of mid-on for a quick single
N Thushara to Rahul, 1 run, fuller than a length on middle, slower ball, and Rahul knocks it to mid-on
Anshul Kamboj, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Anshul Kamboj to Rahul, 1 run, back of a length on middle and leg, Rahul shuffles across and tucks it into the midwicket region
Anshul Kamboj to Stoinis, no run, back of a length delivery just outside off, blocked from the crease
Anshul Kamboj to Stoinis, FOUR, back of a length delivery on off, not very short but Stoinis manages to pull it through midwicket for four
Anshul Kamboj to Stoinis, FOUR, consecutive fours! This is pitched up on off, right in the slot, and Stoinis swings through the line to hit it over the bowler's head
Anshul Kamboj to Stoinis, FOUR, Stoinis is taking the attack to Kamboj! Good length on off, Stoinis goes straight again and lofts it over mid-on, making it look very easy

Anshul Kamboj to Stoinis, 1 run, 136kph, fuller than a length on middle and leg, and Stoinis lofts it towards long-on who was pushed back to the boundary after the previous delivery. It goes on the bounce to him

Arjun Tendulkar [1.0-0-3-0] is back into the attack
Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, FOUR, oh nicely played. Back of a length on off, Stoinis stays leg-side of it, opens the face and guides it past short third
Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, no run, inswinger down the leg-side, wide called. There is a review from MI who think it touched Stoinis's pad. Yep, they're right
Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, 1 run, full delivery on middle, inswinger, and it's punched firmly down the ground by Stoinis. Long-on cuts it off
Arjun Tendulkar to Rahul, no run, 130.7kph back of a length delivery just outside off, Rahul blocks it to cover
Arjun Tendulkar to Rahul, 1 run, full ball just outside off, Rahul looks to drive but mistimes it off the inside half to midwicket
Arjun Tendulkar to Stoinis, 1 run, direct hit from Surya at the non-striker's end but Stoinis is well home. Pitched up just outside off, driven wide of mid-off and he makes the single comfortably
Piyush Chawla, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chawla to Stoinis, 1 run, tossed up and drifting into the pads, 88kph, and Stoinis works it through midwicket
Chawla to Rahul, no run, 86kph, tossed up on leg stump, overpitched, and Rahul drives to mid-off
Chawla to Rahul, SIX, Rahul picks his spot. Googly on off, he walks across the stumps, gets low and sweeps it over square leg who is inside the ring. It goes all the way
Midwicket comes in, square leg goes back
Chawla to Rahul, SIX, tossed up at 84kph, Rahul dances down, takes it on the full and launches it over long-off. Massive hit!
Chawla to Rahul, 1 run, steps out again but isn't to the pitch this time. Quietly nudges it down to long-on
Chawla to Stoinis, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Chawla to Stoinis, out Lbw!! Stoinis misses the sweep and is caught plumb in front! Chawla has his arms aloft in celebration as he adds to his tally of 10 wickets this season. It's a googly tossed up on off, he goes for the slog-sweep but is hit on the back leg. Finger goes up immediately from the umpire. Stoinis doesn't bother with the review. Stoinis lbw b Chawla 28(22) [4s-5]

Deepak Hooda, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Nehal Wadhera, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Nehal Wadhera to Rahul, no run, close to the blockhole on off, Rahul squeezes it out
Nehal Wadhera to Rahul, no run, tossed up outside off, driven to cover

Nehal Wadhera to Rahul, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, Rahul knocks it through cover
Nehal Wadhera to Hooda, 1 run, flat length ball sliding in on middle, Hooda punches it to long-on
Nehal Wadhera to Rahul, 1 run, half-tracker on leg stump, and Rahul can't capitalise as he mistimes the pull to deep square leg

Chawla to Rahul, 1 run, full on off, Rahul looks to drive through cover but drags it off a thick inside edge through midwicket
Chawla to Hooda, 1 run, full ball drifting in on middle and off, Hooda knocks it to long-on
Nehal Wadhera to Hooda, 1 run, tossed up outside off, very full, and it's driven to sweeper cover
Nehal Wadhera to Rahul, 1 run, tossed up on off, lands in the blockhole and Rahul squeezes it to long-on
"Thoda jaldi daal (hurry up)" is the cry from Kishan
Nehal Wadhera to Hooda, 1 run, length ball on off, Hooda punches to cover and they scamper across for the single. There's a direct hit at the striker's end but Rahul is safely home
Nehal Wadhera to Rahul, 1 run, tossed up outside off, Rahul pushes it through cover
Nehal Wadhera to Hooda, 1 run, driven down to long-off
Nehal Wadhera to Rahul, 1 run, not short enough to cut, Rahul goes for it and mistimes it through cover. Just six singles. LSG happy to knock it around against the part timer

Timeout! It's another one of those pitches at the Wankhede where the ball isn't quite coming on. But the intent is also lacking from LSG. Wadhera, who's never bowled before in a T20, has turned up with a couple of quiet overs here.
Chawla to Rahul, no run, flat on off, length ball tuirning away, Rahul makes room and punches it to backward point
Chawla to Rahul, 1 run, tossed up on middle, Rahul plays a lofted drive over the bowler but long-off cuts it off
Chawla to Hooda, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chawla to Hooda, out Caught by Nehal Wadhera!! Chawla strikes again! Good jumping catch from Wadhera at backward point but he has hurt himself after falling on his back. Tossed up outside off, Hooda is made to reach out for the drive, plays well in front of the body and slices it off the outside half. It's going over Wadhera who leaps and hangs on with both hands. Thankfully he doesn't seem to be badly hurt. Hooda c Nehal Wadhera b Chawla 11(9) [4s-1]

Nicholas Pooran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Chawla to Pooran, no run, full outside off, Pooran looks to go for the big shot straightaway but drags it off the inside half to midwicket. Was looking to launch it down the ground
Chawla to Pooran, no run, flat on off, back of a length, and Pooran punches it down the pitch
Chawla to Pooran, no run, tossed up on middle and off, 88kph, Pooran gets forward and defends
Anshul Kamboj [1.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Anshul Kamboj to Rahul, no run, fuller than a length on middle, driven back to Kamboj
Anshul Kamboj to Rahul, 1 run, short of length on off, Rahul advances down and tries flat-batting it hard. But he mistimes it to long-on
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, wide, short and wide, left alone, and it's called wide
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, wide, very wide full toss outside off, left alone
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, wide, another wide outside off

Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, SIX, this is why he didn't want to bowl it closer to Pooran. Short of length just outside off, Pooran shuffles across and nails the pull shot over square leg. That's gone into the second tier
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, no run, wide yorker outside off, sliced to point
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, 1 run, wide yorker outside off again, Pooran reaches out and slices it to deep third
Anshul Kamboj to Rahul, 1 run, 136.3kph, fuller than a length on middle, and Rahul punches it to long-on
MI need to get a move on with the over rate. Even by this tournament's standards it's bad
Hardik Pandya, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Rahul, 2 runs, close to the blockhole outside off, Rahul drives well and it takes a good diving effort at the boundary to cut it off
Hardik Pandya to Rahul, 2 runs, back of a length outside off, slower one, and Rahul cuts it to the left of sweeper cover. Easy couple of runs

Hardik Pandya to Rahul, 2 runs, more work for sweeper cover and it's another excellent effort from Shepherd. Length ball outside off, driven sweetly through extra cover and it's a long chase for Shepherd in the deep. He charges across to his left and dives to cut it off
Hardik Pandya to Rahul, 1 run, length ball on off, Rahul knocks it to long-on
Hardik Pandya to Pooran, 1 run, 130.4kph, full outside off, Pooran looks to launch it down the ground but is early through the shot. Mistimes it off the toe-end down the ground
Hardik Pandya to Rahul, FOUR, Rahul walks across the stumps, gets a low full toss on middle and flicks it past short fine leg. Welcome runs for him
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, FOUR, inside edge past the stumps! Full and wide, Pooran premeditates by moving across the stumps and looks to shovel it over square leg. Gets lucky
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, no run, wide yorker outside off, squeezed to cover
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, wide, another wide yorker, but this one's outside the marker. Pooran leaves it alone
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, FOUR, same ball attempted, execution is only slightly off as he's a few inches short, but that's enough for Pooran. He reaches out and slices it over short third

Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, SIX, oh this is glorious! Full and wide outside off, few inches short of the blockhole, Pooran reaches out and carves it over extra cover. The timing is so good that it sails over the ropes

Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, SIX, six over point this time! Would it have been a chance if the fielder was all the way back at the boundary? He was standing a few yards inside, or maybe he misjudged it and came in. Full toss outside off, Pooran reahces out and slaps it in the air. Goes over a back-pedaling Brevis
Anshul Kamboj to Pooran, 1 run, yorker outside off, squeezed to sweeper cover
Hardik Pandya to Pooran, SIX, Pooran is on fire. A length delivery angling away from him, he gets forward and flays it over sweeper cover, flies away
Hardik Pandya to Pooran, 1 run, low full-toss around off, Pooran loses his shape as he tries to swing, gets it down to long-on
Hardik Pandya to Rahul, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on a length outside off, Rahul chops the cut to the point region
Hardik Pandya to Pooran, SIX, just over deep mid-wicket. His 5th six. A length delivery on the stumps, Pooran heaves it over the man on the fence
Hardik Pandya to Pooran, 1 run, a low full-toss just outside off, Pooran drives to sweeper cover
Hardik Pandya to Rahul, no run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Rahul cuts and misses
Arjun Tendulkar [2.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Arjun Tendulkar has pulled up while running in to bowl. The physio is out there. That's why the delay.
Arjun Tendulkar to Pooran, SIX, into the second-deck. A friendly low full-toss and angling into the pads, Pooran swings it with glee over the deep backward square leg fence

Arjun Tendulkar to Pooran, SIX, 50 for Pooran! He is blowing flying kisses to someone. Another poor delivery - low full-toss on the stumps, Pooran heaves again to the deep backward square leg fence. So easy
Arjun Tendulkar is off. On comes Rohit to field with a smile on his face. Tendulkar is struggling and the physio is out attending to him. Naman Dhir to complete this over.
Naman Dhir, right-arm off break, comes into the attack

Naman Dhir to Pooran, SIX, Pooran is on tonight. And there are very few in the world in this format who can match him when he is on. A tossed up delivery outside the leg-stump, Pooran makes room and slogsweeps way back over deep square leg. Hat-trick of sixes
Naman Dhir to Pooran, FOUR, just inside the ropes at deep extra-cover. It's tossed up full outside off, Pooran goes over extra-cover, superbly hit, but can't get it all the way
Naman Dhir to Pooran, 1 run, yorker length outside off, jammed out to his left and they take a quick single
Naman Dhir to Rahul, SIX, 29 off the over. Now Rahul goes after Naman Dhir, comes down the track and it's tossed up and he lofts clean and high over wide long-on, 4th six of the over

Summary (Overs 7-15) > MI keep LSG under check even post powerplay > Hooda becomes Chawla’s 2nd victim > Pooran unfurls his wings with a flurry of boundaries > Pooran races to a 19-ball 50 > 29 runs off the 15th over as LSG score 6-6-6-4-1-6

Shepherd to Pooran, no run, full outside off, from round the wicket, Pooran shuffles across to heave and misses, good first ball
Shepherd to Pooran, wide, this is wide of the tramline on the off-side as Pooran lets it go

Shepherd to Rahul, FOUR, 50 for Rahul! A slower ball is a low full-toss outside off, swiped hard and flat, deep mid-wicket dives to his left but the ball lands in front of the hand and slips away
Shepherd to Rahul, wide, wide of the crease and full outside off, outside the tramline, another wide

Shepherd to Rahul, no run, look at the reaction of the crowd as Rohit at backward point dives to his right and saves four. Another low full-toss outside off, similar square drive by Rahul but Rohit saves four. The crowd roar in unison
Timeout! Pooran's assault has given LSG the platform to go mad here. 225 is on from here.

Nuwan Thushara [2.0-0-11-1] is back into the attack
N Thushara to Pooran, no run, yorker length just outside off, Pooran mistimes the drive back to N Thushara
N Thushara to Pooran, no run, full slower ball off-cutter just outside off, Pooran heaves and it doesn't go far, finds the fielder inside the ring at square leg

N Thushara to Pooran, FOUR, full slower ball off-cutter outside off, Pooran again doesn't get it off the middle, he swings and a thick inside-edge runs through square leg and goes to the fence, beating the fielder in the deep on the leg-side
N Thushara to Pooran, FOUR, full and in the slot outside off, Pooran lofts over extra-cover and it's a clean strike, and no chance for long-off to his right
N Thushara to Pooran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

N Thushara to Pooran, out Caught by Suryakumar Yadav!! Full and wide on the tramline, Pooran doesn't want to leave that, shuffles across to loft and finds SKY at long-on. Good overhead catch as SKY took it well and he was just inches from the cushions. Fine innings comes to an end and SKY has a lengthy chat with Pooran as the batter walks off. Pandya too appreciates the knock, as he pats Pooran on the head. Pooran c Suryakumar Yadav b N Thushara 75(29) [4s-5 6s-8]

N Thushara to Arshad Khan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

N Thushara to Arshad Khan, out Caught by Nehal Wadhera!! Two in two. Wadhera at cover nearly makes a meal of it, but takes it on the 2nd attempt. Full and wide outside off, Arshad Khan toe-ends the loft and Wadhera had a simple catch as he went to his left from cover, dropped it the 1st time but hung on to the rebound. Thushara smiles wryly. Piyush Chawla [3.0-0-21-2] is back into the attack
Chawla to Rahul, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chawla to Rahul, out Caught by N Thushara!! Team hat-trick. It's tossed up full on the stumps, Rahul goes for a big sweep and the top-edge goes straight to the fielder at short fine-leg. Thushara in the thick of action. Suddenly LSG have lost their way. Rahul c N Thushara b Chawla 55(41) [4s-3 6s-3]
Krunal Pandya, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Chawla to Krunal Pandya, SIX, what a blow first ball. It's tossed up full outside off, Krunal Pandya does not hold back as he gets forward and lofts straight down the ground, no-one is catching that
A slip in.
Chawla to Krunal Pandya, no run, tossed up full on the stumps, Krunal Pandya gets forward to defend

N Thushara to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, the hat-trick ball is a full delivery on the stumps, drilled to mid-on's left, he dives and stops, direct-hit and Ayush Badoni was gone, even half a chance to run Krunal Pandya out was there, but the throw missed both stumps
N Thushara to Krunal Pandya, no run, slower ball wide outside off, Krunal Pandya shuffles across to swipe and he misses, the ball goes under the bat
N Thushara to Krunal Pandya, FOUR, slower and shorter on the stumps, Krunal Pandya gets inside the line and pulls to the deep backward square leg fence, that area is unmanned
N Thushara to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, a low full-toss outside off, Krunal Pandya reaches for it and drives, third man is there

N Thushara to Ayush Badoni, 2 runs, slower ball off-cutter on the pads, flicked wide of deep backward square leg and the 2nd was a tight one, the throw comes to Ishan Kishan who backflicks and had he found the target, Ayush Badoni was gone
N Thushara to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter full on the stumps, driven to long-on and Ayush Badoni retains the strike with that run
Romario Shepherd [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Shepherd to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, full outside off, Ayush Badoni shuffles across and mistimes the heave, just a single to long-on
Shepherd to Krunal Pandya, 2 wides, full and down leg, Krunal Pandya flicks and misses, Ishan Kishan fumbles and they take one more
Shepherd to Ayush Badoni, SIX, super shot. Full and wide outside off, Ayush Badoni moves across and lofts on a bent back knee, flies over sweeper cover and LSG cross 200. Glorious shot

Shepherd to Ayush Badoni, SIX, just over and wide of the leaping long-off to his left. Full and in the slot outside off, Ayush Badoni lofts and has enough to clear the outstretched left hand of the leaping Brevis
Shepherd now round the wicket.
Shepherd to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, the angle changes but the line doesn't. Full outside off, slogged over mid-wicket and no-one there at deep mid-wicket. Big over this
LSG review for a non-wide. Well inside the tramline.
Shepherd to Ayush Badoni, no run, good ball, well inside the tramline, full outside off, left alone and the review is burnt
Shepherd to Ayush Badoni, no run, two dots to end. Good full delivery just outside off, Ayush Badoni shuffles across to sweep, misses, the ball misses off-stump as well

21:30 Local Time, 16:00 GMT, 21:30 IST: LSG will be happy with this score despite losing three in three late on. Padikkal's horror season ended with a duck in the first over. Stoinis looked good till he fell LBW to Chawla and Hooda disappointed again. Till then KL was in his shell and scoring at less than 100. Suddenly he flicked a switch and hit consecutive sixes off Chawla to get going. But the innings that really sparked LSG's score was Pooran's. He showed why he is so destructive in this format as he clouted sixes at will - 8 in total. He struck them cleanly and his knock suddenly catapulted LSG and set them on their way to 230-240 but his dismissal sparked a mini collapse before Ayush Badoni and Krunal Pandya added cameos to take LSG to 214. Pandya may have missed a trick at not bowling more spin when Pooran was there as the quick bowlers were taken apart. Can MI end with a win? Back for the reply in 5 minutes...

Nicholas Pooran: Similar situation to ones I’ve been in over the years. I’ve been training a lot and practicing hitting a lot of sixes. Blessed that I’m talented in that. I always enjoy myself and want to be the best version of myself. Need to understand where the game is going and how everyone else is playing as well. Today is all about enjoying and having fun, not much to tell the bowlers. It’s about executing our plans. I’d very much want this to be a good score.
Welcome back. Rohit is the impact player for MI. Brevis is his partner. That's a surprise. Naveen is the impact player for LSG. Arshad Khan will start. A wide slip.
